  "local_port": 46062,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How to reset Honeywell thermostat and erase schedule?",
  "response": "Resetting a Honeywell thermostat and erasing its schedule can depend on the specific model you have. Below are general steps for resetting Honeywell thermostats, including erasing schedules for common models:\n\n### Resetting a Honeywell Thermostat\n\n#### For Honeywell RTH Series (RTH9585WF, RTH9580WF, etc.):\n1. **Access the Menu:**\n   - Press the **\"Menu\"** button on the touchscreen.\n\n2. **Navigate to Reset:**\n   - Use the **arrow buttons** to scroll to **\"Settings.\"**\n   - Select **\"Reset\"** or **\"Restore Factory Settings.\"**\n\n3. **Erase Schedules:**\n   - In the reset options, look for **\"Delete All Schedule\"** or **\"Clear Schedule.\"**\n   - Confirm the selection to erase the schedules.\n\n#### For Honeywell Round Thermostats (TH110, TH300, etc.):\n1. **Access the Thermostat:**\n   - Press the **\"Set\"** button to enter the settings.\n\n2. **Factory Reset:**\n   - Use the **\"+\" or \"-\"** buttons to navigate to the reset option.\n   - Select **\"Reset\"** or **\"Restore Factory Settings.\"**\n  \n3. **Erase Schedules (if applicable):**\n   - Depending on the model, you may need to navigate to the schedule settings and manually delete any set schedules.\n\n#### For Honeywell Wi-Fi Thermostats:\n1. **Access the Menu:**\n   - Tap the **\"Menu\"** button on the screen.\n\n2. **Go to Settings:**\n   - Scroll down and select **\"Settings.\"**\n\n3. **Factory Reset:**\n   - Look for **\"Reset\"** or **\"Factory Reset.\"**\n   - Confirm to proceed.\n\n4. **Erase Schedules:**\n   - Again, there might be a specific option to **\"Delete Schedule.\"**\n\n### General Tips:\n- Always check your user manual for specific instructions related to your model.\n- A reset will return the thermostat to default settings, including any saved Wi-Fi information and temperature preferences.\n- If you are unsure about the procedure for your specific model, you can usually find the user manual online at Honeywell's official website.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, or if the steps differ from the options shown above, please refer to the user manual specific to your Honeywell thermostat model, or contact Honeywell customer support for further assistance.",
